### Self-learning loop

This CLI caches per-question discovery so repeat queries skip the walk and structurally similar queries get answered via entity substitution. Agents call `recall` before discovery and fire `teach &` after answering. See the `## Automatic learning` section in `SKILL.md` for the four-branch protocol.

- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli recall <query>`** - Look up cached resources for a query before running discovery
- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli teach`** - Record a query -> resource mapping (silent on success, safe to background with `&`)
- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli learnings list`** - Inspect taught rows
- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli learnings forget <query>`** - Undo a teach
- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli teach-pattern`** - Install a query/resource template up front
- **`{{$.Name}}-pp-cli teach-lookup`** - Add an entity mapping (e.g. country code, team alias) for pattern substitution

Pass `--no-learn` or set `{{envPrefix .Name}}_NO_LEARN=true` to disable the loop for deterministic flows.
{{- end}}

